@Machiavelli1 - Your screenshots are clearly indicating that the characters are too long and cannot exceed X amount of characters. Try the Extract To option and give a new folder name, feel free to try the Extract Here option first.....

@dougcjohn - I will assume you burned in Windows....the contents sometimes show blank because the ISO should be based on HFS file system (could be hybrid ISO with ISO9660 and HFS). If you use a program like UltraISO you will see the contents, or even MacDrive. 

@hish123 - Same as above (dougcjohn); if you're mounting in Windows there's a high chance you won't see the contents. Use MacDrive and you should see whatever it is you're looking for. 

*Remember to burn DVD at lowest speed (recommended 2x if available or 4x). 

